    <section class="section section--alt">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2>Parking</h2>
          <p>There's ample parking available in and around the town centre.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid--2">
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>Town Centre Car Parks</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>London Road</strong> — Large car park close to the castle and town centre. Short and long-stay options available.</li>
              <li><strong>Riverside</strong> — Near the River Trent, convenient for castle and riverside walks.</li>
              <li><strong>Appletongate</strong> — Central location with easy access to the Market Square.</li>
              <li><strong>Castle House</strong> — Council car park, centrally located.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>All car parks are clearly signposted with reasonable fees. Many offer pay-and-display or pay-by-phone options.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-card">
            <h3>Tips for Visitors</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>On market days (Mon, Wed, Thu, Fri, Sat), town centre parking can be busier — arrive early or use the larger car parks.</li>
              <li>On-street parking is available on some roads with time restrictions — check signs carefully.</li>
              <li>Both railway stations have their own car parks if you're combining rail and road travel.</li>
              <li>The town centre is very walkable — most attractions are within 10 minutes' walk of the Market Square.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

